data.name: GeneralStatusDesc_0x00
data.value: Service was successfully performed by the object specified

data.name: GeneralStatusDesc_0x01
data.value: A connection related service failed along the connection path.

data.name: GeneralStatusDesc_0x02
data.value: Resources needed for the object to perform the requested service were unavailable.

data.name: GeneralStatusDesc_0x03
data.value: A parameter associated with the request was invalid. This code is used when a parameter does not meet the requirements of this specification and/or the requirements defined in an Application Object Specification.

data.name: GeneralStatusDesc_0x04
data.value: The path segment identifier or the segment syntax was not understood by the processing node. Path processing shall stop when a path segment error is encountered.

data.name: GeneralStatusDesc_0x05
data.value: The path is referencing an object class, instance, or structure element that is not known or is not contained in the processing node. Path processing shall stop when a path destination unknown error is encountered.

data.name: GeneralStatusDesc_0x06
data.value: Only part of the expected data was transferred.

data.name: GeneralStatusDesc_0x07
data.value: The messaging connection was lost.

data.name: GeneralStatusDesc_0x08
data.value: The requested service was not implemented or was not defined for this Object Class/Instance.

data.name: GeneralStatusDesc_0x09
data.value: Invalid attribute data detected.

data.name: GeneralStatusDesc_0x0A
data.value: An attribute in the Get_Attribute_List or Set_Attribute_List response has a non-zero status.

data.name: GeneralStatusDesc_0x0B
data.value: The object is already in the mode/state being requested by the service.

data.name: GeneralStatusDesc_0x0C
data.value: The object cannot perform the requested service in its current mode/state.

data.name: GeneralStatusDesc_0x0D
data.value: The requested instance of the object to be created already exists.

data.name: GeneralStatusDesc_0x0E
data.value: A request to modify a non-modifiable attribute was received.

data.name: GeneralStatusDesc_0x0F
data.value: A permission/privilage check failed.

data.name: GeneralStatusDesc_0x10
data.value: The devices current mode/state prohibits the execution of the requested service.

data.name: GeneralStatusDesc_0x11
data.value: The data to be transmitted in the response buffer is larger than the allocated response buffer.

data.name: GeneralStatusDesc_0x12
data.value: The service specified an operation that is going to fragment a primitive data value, i.e. half a REAL data type.

data.name: GeneralStatusDesc_0x13
data.value: The service did not supply enough data to perform the specified operation.

data.name: GeneralStatusDesc_0x14
data.value: The attribute specified in the request is not supported.

data.name: GeneralStatusDesc_0x15
data.value: The service supplied more data than was expected.

data.name: GeneralStatusDesc_0x16
data.value: The object specified does not exist in the device.

data.name: GeneralStatusDesc_0x17
data.value: The fragmentation sequence for this service is not currently active for this data.

data.name: GeneralStatusDesc_0x18
data.value: The attribute data of this object was not saved prior to the requested service.

data.name: GeneralStatusDesc_0x19
data.value: The attribute data of this object was not saved due to a failure during the attempt.

data.name: GeneralStatusDesc_0x1A
data.value: The service request packet was too large for transmission on a network in the path to the destination. The routing device was forced to abort the service.

data.name: GeneralStatusDesc_0x1B
data.value: The service response packet was too large for transmission on a network in the path to the destination. The routing device was forced to abort the service.

data.name: GeneralStatusDesc_0x1C
data.value: The service did not supply an attribute in a list of attributes that was needed by the service to perform the requested behavior.

data.name: GeneralStatusDesc_0x1D
data.value: The service is returning the list of attributes supplied with status information for those attributes that were invalid.

data.name: GeneralStatusDesc_0x1E
data.value: An embedded service resulted in an error.

data.name: GeneralStatusDesc_0x1F
data.value: A vendor specific error has occurred.

data.name: GeneralStatusDesc_0x20
data.value: A parameter associated with the request was invalid.

data.name: GeneralStatusDesc_0x21
data.value: An attempt was made to write to a write-once medium (e.g.WORM drive, PROM) that has already been written, or to modify a value that cannot be changed once established.

data.name: GeneralStatusDesc_0x22
data.value: An invalid reply is received (e.g. reply service code does not mach the request service code, or reply message is shorter than the minimum expected reply size).

data.name: GeneralStatusDesc_0x25
data.value: The Key Segment that was included as the first segment in the path does not match the destination module. The object specific status shall indicate which part of the key check failed.

data.name: GeneralStatusDesc_0x26
data.value: The size of the path which was sent with the Service Request is either not large enough to allow the Request to be routed to an object or too much routing data was included.

data.name: GeneralStatusDesc_0x27
data.value: An attempt was made to set an attribute that is not able to be set at this time.

data.name: GeneralStatusDesc_0x28
data.value: The Member ID specified in the request does not exist in the specified Class/Instance/Attribute.

data.name: GeneralStatusDesc_0x29
data.value: A request to modify a non-modifiable member was received.

data.name: GeneralStatusDesc_0x2A
data.value: This error may be reported by DeviceNet group 2 only servers with 4K or less code space and only in place of Service Not Supported, Attribute Not Supported, and Attribute Not Settable.
